Orlando Pirates have confirmed the signing of four new players as they continue to strengthen the team ahead of the new season. The Soweto giants have signed strikers Evidence Makgopa, Bienvenu Eva Nga, midfielder Miguel Timm and winger Azola Matrose. The quartet will form part of preseason preparations which commence this week, the club confirmed. Meanwhile, the club will also be letting go of six players to make space for new arrivals which include defenders Tapelo Xoki and Nkosinathi Sibisi. The pair were announced last week, and they join Bucs from KwaZulu-Natal sides AmaZulu and Golden Arrows. Pirates confirmed that Kwanda Mngonyama, Abel Mabaso, Justice Chabalala, Elson Sithole, Wayne Sandilands and Thabang Monare will not be part of the new season. “Sandilands’ contract comes to an end on June 30 and will not be renewed however, the Club is currently in discussions with Management regarding another role at the Club,” read a statement on the club’s website.” “The Club can also confirm that contractual discussions with Monare have collapsed as the two parties could not agree on terms. The Club would like to wish the players well in their future endeavours.”